public void queue(BatchRequest batch,
                  JsonBatchCallback<Task> callback)
           throws IOException
Queues the "get" request to the Taskqueue server into the given batch request.

Example usage: 

         request.queue(batchRequest, new JsonBatchCallback<Task>() {

           public void onSuccess(Task content, GoogleHeaders responseHeaders) {
             log("Success");
           }

           public void onFailure(GoogleJsonError e, GoogleHeaders responseHeaders) {
             log(e.getMessage());
           }
         });
